The Financial Stability Oversight Council (FSOC) also recognizes
the need for legislation. At a hearing in May 2022, then Treasury
Secretary Janet Yellen testified before the Committee in her capac-
ity as Chair of FSOC and underscored the urgency of stablecoin
legislation, explaining that FSOC is ‘‘eager to work with [the Com-
mittee] to ensure that payment stablecoins and their arrangements
are subject to a federal prudential framework on a consistent and
comprehensive basis.’’ FSOC emphasized this point in its October
2022 Report on Digital Asset Financial Stability Risks and Regula-
